    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen I open a preview of a file from netrw and that file is modified, if I then try to open a preview of another file I get an error:\n```\nError in function <SNR>61_NetrwPreview:\nline   31:\nE37: No write since last change (add ! to override)\n```\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n`nvim --clean`\n`:Explore`\n`p` (on file A)\ngo to that file and do any change, **don't save**\ngo back to Netrw window\n`p` (on file B)\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nCurrently previewed file (the modified one) is hidden and a new one is shown.\n(I haven't found any documentation on the topic so it's my expected behavior)\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-2717+ga940b77cb2 Build type: Release LuaJIT 2.1.1772619647\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nyes, vim 9.2\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS Tahoe 26.3.1 (25D2128) arm64\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nGhostty 1.3.2-main+bebca8466\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-ghostty\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo (with distclean)",
